World Wide Fund for Nature launched a partnership called Herd of One with Sankara Hotel Nairobi to enhance elephant conservation and the livelihoods of people who live in and around elephant-rich areas. The event was held at the Sankara Hotel in Nairobi on December 17. In attendance was the group general manager of Sankara Hotel, Krishna Uuni, and director, Business Development & Communications - WWF-Kenya Joyce Isiaho. Sankara Hotel director Rohan Patel urged the attendees to help them rope more individuals to the initiative to save more elephants and educate people on the benefits of taking care of wild animals.